    <abstract>
      <t>This document describes extensions to Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) for flooding the link states on a topology that is a subgraph of the complete topology of a BGP-SPF domain, so that the amount of flooding traffic in the domain is greatly reduced. This would reduce convergence time with a more stable and optimized routing environment.</t>
